                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221023-108-off574 t18221023-108-crimeloc577"></join>. On the 26th of September, between eleven and twelve o'clock at night, the prisoner came in; I did not see him; I was sitting behind the counter. My coat and waistcoat hung nearly at the back of the counter; he was brought back with it directly.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221023-108-person1124">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HAWKINS
               <interp inst="t18221023-108-person1124" type="surname" value="HAWKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221023-108-person1124" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221023-108-person1124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a servant to Charlotte. I saw the prisoner come into the house, between eleven and twelve o'clock; he went behind the counter, where my master was dosing - I saw him go out. I ran out, caught him with the coat and waistcoat under his jacket, about six yards off.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded distress.</p>
